title: Heights eyes 3-0; Panthers start district
text: Heights eyes 3-0; Panthers start district Published: Wednesday, October 14, 2015 5:15 PM CDT Valley Heights, 2-4, has a chance to take a 3-0 lead in 2-1A district play in a 7 p.m. kickoff Friday against visiting Alma-Wabaunsee, 1-5, while both Centralia and Washington County kickoff 3A district.Centralia, 3-3 after a 59-13 loss to No. 1 and undefeated Rossville in 3A, has a 7 p.m. start against visiting Nemaha Central, 6-0. Twin Valley League champion Washington County, 6-0, kicks off against guest Riley County, 4-2. Valley Heights 19, Onaga 6 Valley Heights built a 16-0 lead in the first half on junior Hunter Stevenson’s 56-yard run, sophomore Jordan Yungeberg’s 30-yard run and junior Frederik Bjerg’s 20-yard field goal. Bjerg kicked a 31-yarder in the fourth quarter. Onaga’s score was a Garrett Ames 2-yard run. VH 13 3 0 3 — 19OHS 0 0 6 0 — 6 V O
